## Common Pitfalls

**The agent claims lint warnings are "legacy" and skips them**
They're not. Stop, and make it fix them.

**The agent modifies test files during the Green phase**
This is suspicious - Green should only add production code. Question any test changes.

**The conversation compacts or summarises**
HARD STOP. Start a new conversation. Provide the previous prompt and tell the agent to pick up from where it left off. The planning documents carry the context and make re-starting simple.

**The agent makes code changes without running a skill**
Stop. All code changes should go through a framework skill (build, bug, refactor, refine). Not just for the rigour, but to keep the documentation aligned with the code. 

The LLM will follow instructions, so it's easy to override any process. If you're working on non-production code and want to skip TDD, then tell it to skip. I don't advise overrides for prod code, but if you do then the framework rules are to find the relevant design doc and note the override before complying.

